Create gene_lookup.py

Create make_fpkm_matrix.py

Formatting and filtering individual single cell fpkm files into fpkm matrix files.  Output to tab delimited csv and/or pickle for easy use and downstream analysis.

Create tophat_qsub.py

Generates qsub commands for cluster submission.

Create sort_fpkm.py

For lots of RNA-seq files (single cell). This will walk through a directory and sort the fpkm_tracking files output from cufflinks by gene name and write a new file for each.

Create process_reads.py

This function is mainly for file path parsing.  Creates named output files for each set of reads. 

Files are named for cell number: C10_fastq
Reads are in that file with format: L2_GCTACGCTCTCTCTAT_L002_R1_001.fastq.gz

Needs lots of customizing for different systems.

Create fpkm_merge.py

fpkm_merge is a function that takes a file of fpkm tracking files from single cell RNA seq runs and outputs two files: one with all of the fpkm values for each cell/condition/timepoint and one with info for each cell.  These files can then be used with monocle (http://monocle-bio.sourceforge.net/) or Singular (http://www.fluidigm.com/singular-analysis-toolset.html) to do analysis (PCA, clustering, etc.)

Create Gene_ontology_lookup.py

This script uses biopython entrez to fetch all of the associated gene ontology (GO) terms for a gene or list of genes from the NCBI gene database.
